<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="105">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1896" class="Insecta" family="Vitaceae" genus="Presbistus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Presbistus" order="Phasmatodea" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Presbistus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other members of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1893" family="Aschiphasmatidae" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Phasmida" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Aschiphasmatinae">Aschiphasmatinae</taxonomicName>
by the combination of the following set of characters (adapted from 
<bibRefCitation author="Bragg, PE" journalOrPublisher="Natural History Publications (Borneo), Kota Kinabalu" pageId="0" pageNumber="105" refId="B6" refString="Bragg, PE, 2001. Phasmids of Borneo. Natural History Publications (Borneo), Kota Kinabalu" title="Phasmids of Borneo." year="2001">Bragg 2001</bibRefCitation>
):
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Body and legs brown with some black markings.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Mesonotum unarmed.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Profemora incurving at base; all femora with distinct medioventral carina, armed with at least a few minute spines.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Tegmina triangular and spine-like; anal region of hind wing translucent brown.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Apex of male abdomen distinctly swollen.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Apex of female abdomen almost arrowhead shaped in dorsal view. Subgenital plate with anterior portion globose, posterior half medially keeled and tapering.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Cerci cylindrical.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="105">Eggs longer than high, lacking setae.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
